## Step 1: To rationalize the denominator, multiply the fraction by 1 in the form of the denominator over itself.
$\sqrt{\frac23}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac23}}{1}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac23}}{\sqrt{\frac23}}$
## Step 2: $\frac{\sqrt{\frac23}}{\sqrt{\frac23}}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac23}\sqrt{\frac23}}{\left(\sqrt{\frac23}\right)\left(\sqrt{\frac23}\right)}$
## Step 3: $\frac{\sqrt{\frac23}\sqrt{\frac23}}{\left(\sqrt{\frac23}\right)\left(\sqrt{\frac23}\right)}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac23\cdot\frac23}}{\frac23}$
## Step 4: $\frac{\sqrt{\frac23\cdot\frac23}}{\frac23}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac4{9}}}{\frac23}$
$=\frac{\frac{\sqrt4}{\sqrt9}}{\frac23}$
$=\frac{\frac{2}{3}}{\frac23}$
$=\frac{\frac{2}{3}}{\frac23}=\frac{2}{3}\div\frac{2}{3}$
## Step 5: $\frac{2}{3}\div\frac{2}{3}=\frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{3}{2}=1$
The final answer is: $\boxed{1}$
